Stephen Sondheim wrote the West Side Story lyrics at 25. His lyrics made Broadway at 27 in 1957. Then he wrote the lyrics to Gypsy. 

Then wrote his own music. 

He was mentored by Oscar Hammerstein. 

In return, he mentored Jonathan Larson and so many other composers.
